snippet.textDisplay:
I recently watched a video showing the performance and range evolution of the Model S, and you can't help but to be impressed with how dramatically Tesla has improved (and all pushed the other EV manufacturers to do the same). https://youtu.be/7-XMnUrFp5U

Keep in mind that these EVs (including the Model S) are 4 door sedans. As fun as it is to see an EV beat a 6 figure (cost) sports car the average consumer will prefer them based on the practicality of a very capable car .....which as an extra benefit can still overtake the geriatric driving the lambo.

Later this year, it will be interesting to see how a Nuremberg tuned Tesla roadster and Model S perform. I am sure many of the comments I read in this thread will not age well...
